{
  "_doc": "Edge of Eternities (EOE) Play + Collector recipes. Source: https://magic.wizards.com/en/news/feature/collecting-edge-of-eternities . Lineup is authoritative: EOE had Play Boosters + Collector Boosters and NO Draft Boosters. Sub-set codes: EOE = main set, EOS = Stellar Sights bonus sheet (45 lands), SPG = Special Guests, EOC = EOE Commander, TEOE = tokens. Percentages match Wizards' verbatim odds (entries the article gave as '<1%' are modeled as 0.1). Re-pointing: the Stellar Sights 'Galaxy Foil' and 'Poster Galaxy Foil' outcomes now carry the galaxy_foil filter, and the 'Japan Showcase Fracture Foil' outcome now uses the fracture_foil filter (article confirms galaxy foil on Stellar Sights lands and a 1% fracture-foil Japan Showcase). Remaining approximations: the 'Viewport', 'Triumphant', and 'Surreal' booster-fun treatments all collapse to the borderless filter (engine can't distinguish them) and 'extended-art' booster-fun -> extended_art; 'Celestial' basics -> basic_land (kept in their land slot, so their galaxy-foil variant stays on basic_land rather than galaxy_foil); plain (non-fracture) Japan Showcase -> japanese filter; 'Viewport Galaxy Foil' stays on the borderless filter (can't express borderless + galaxy_foil together) and 'poster' / 'singularity' finishes have no dedicated filter. Textless singularity-foil Sothera modeled with a plain outcome. Stellar Sights cards reference the EOS set. AUDIT 2026-06: SPG rate was per common sub-pull (×6 overpull); articles state it per PLAY BOOSTER — now 0.3 per slot (1.8/6). AUDIT 2026-06: Special Guests outcomes re-pointed to set SPG + spg_eoe (collector range — sheets verified by release date). The previous special_guest promo filter matched zero prints, and unranged SPG pulls would leak other sets’ guests. AUDIT 2026-06: special-finish outcome rarities corrected to match the actual printed sheets (pool-verified): fracture_foil->mythic. AUDIT 2026-06 (article re-verification): the Collector default rare/mythic slot and celestial-land outcomes gained their missing foil flags (article: traditional foil). All other slots verified verbatim.",
